A survey shows that people have come from many different parts of the world to live in Slough. Nationalities include:
{ British, Indian, Pakistani, West {Indian, Irish, Dutch, Hungarian, {Canadian, Italian, Polish. }
Because the people come from so many places, there is a wide range of {Religions}(see page 11). Most people live in families of 4, with large families uncommon, but with a number of childless married couples. Many people have{extended families}in Slough with cousins, parents, brothers & sisters etc.. People move to Slough in waves - one 35 years ago, one 10 years ago - but very few people seem to have arrived in the last 10 years.
